            <h1 class="mf-title">For Students</h1>
            <p class="mf-subtitle mf-copy no-bpadding">When we were making the documentary <i>Most Likely To Succeed</i>, we had modest expectations for how it would be received by students. An 87-minute documentary, in a world full of movies like Furious7, didn’t strike us as something students
                would be all over. But they are. So if you’re a student who cares about your future, consider bringing MLTS to your community. The reaction we’ve gotten from our student screenings is, invariably, “How can we show this to our parents and
                teachers? We want our school to be more like this.” We work with student groups to help you bring the film to your school. Consider using the film as a fundraiser for a club or student government.</p>
